alse,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"As, I already checked with support team via portal, due to domain confirmation I checked with them. Here, adding the required information: \n\n##Title: Server-Side Request Forgery in \"icons.bitwarden.net\".\n##URL: https://icons.bitwarden.net/spoofed.burpcollaborator.net/icon.png\n##Parameter: REST based in \"https://icons.bitwarden.net/{DOMAIN-HERE}/icon.png\"\n##Summary: The application failed to validate the vulnerable URL which led to internal port scanning through SSRF vulnerability. \n##Severity: High\n\n##Proof of Concept: \n1. The application shows \"https://icons.bitwarden.net/localhost/icon.png\". - 400 Bad Request.\n2. The application shows https://icons.bitwarden.net/spoofed.burpcollaborator.net/icon.png - 404 Not Found.\nNote: Furthermore, an attacker would be able to perform host discovery and internal port scanning which I did not perform as the scope was not mentioned in the list so better that you can proceed with the above Proof of Concept steps. \n\n##Recommendation:\nIn the above steps, localhost was restricted but was able to bypass using domain \"spoofed.burpcollaborator.net\" which resolves \"127.0.0.1\". The application should resolve the domain and restrict access to internal resources.\n\n## Impact\n\n* An attacker would be able to perform SSRF attack to retrieve internal infrastructure information.","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eAs, I already checked with support team via portal, due to domain confirmation I checked with them. Here, adding the required information: \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"title-server-side-request-forgery-in-icons-bitwarden-net\"\u003eTitle: Server-Side Request Forgery in \u0026quot;icons.bitwarden.net\u0026quot;.\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"url-https-icons-bitwarden-net-spoofed-burpcollaborator-net-icon-png\"\u003eURL: \u003ca title=\"https://icons.bitwarden.net/spoofed.burpcollaborator.net/icon.png\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Ficons.bitwarden.net%2Fspoofed.burpcollaborator.net%2Ficon.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://icons.bitwarden.net/spoofed.burpcollaborator.net/icon.png\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"parameter-rest-based-in-https-icons-bitwarden-net-7bdomain-here-7d-icon-png\"\u003eParameter: REST based in \u0026quot;\u003ca title=\"https://icons.bitwarden.net/%7BDOMAIN-HERE%7D/icon.png\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Ficons.bitwarden.net%2F%257BDOMAIN-HERE%257D%2Ficon.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://icons.bitwarden.net/%7BDOMAIN-HERE%7D/icon.png\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"summary-the-application-failed-to-validate-the-vulnerable-url-which-led-to-internal-port-scanning-through-ssrf-vulnerability\"\u003eSummary: The application failed to validate the vulnerable URL which led to internal port scanning through SSRF vulnerability.\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"severity-high\"\u003eSeverity: High\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"proof-of-concept\"\u003eProof of Concept:\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe application shows \u0026quot;\u003ca title=\"https://icons.bitwarden.net/localhost/icon.png\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Ficons.bitwarden.net%2Flocalhost%2Ficon.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://icons.bitwarden.net/localhost/icon.png\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u0026quot;. - 400 Bad Request.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe application shows \u003ca title=\"https://icons.bitwarden.net/spoofed.burpcollaborator.net/icon.png\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Ficons.bitwarden.net%2Fspoofed.burpcollaborator.net%2Ficon.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://icons.bitwarden.net/spoofed.burpcollaborator.net/icon.png\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e - 404 Not Found.\nNote: Furthermore, an attacker would be able to perform host discovery and internal port scanning which I did not perform as the scope was not mentioned in the list so better that you can proceed with the above Proof of Concept steps. \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"recommendation\"\u003eRecommendation:\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn the above steps, localhost was restricted but was able to bypass using domain \u0026quot;spoofed.burpcollaborator.net\u0026quot; which resolves \u0026quot;127.0.0.1\u0026quot;. The application should resolve the domain and restrict access to internal resources.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"impact\"\u003eImpact\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAn attacker would be able to perform SSRF attack to retrieve internal infrastructure information.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n","weakness":{"id":68,"name":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2020-08-07T14:39:00.820Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-12414666.93796445,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":11,"voters":["jatindhankhar","mygf","sudi","sa1tama0","za_sec","iamcoolcat","pmsecurise","v13rsba","shravs05","sudn","and 1 more..."],"severity":{"rating":"medium","author_type":"Team"},"structured_scope":{"databaseId":767,"asset_type":"URL","asset_identifier":"bitwarden.com","max_severity":"critical"},"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"can_edit_custom_fields_attributes":false,"activities":[{"id":8472279,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::ReportSeverityUpdated","message":"","markdown_message":"","automated_response":false,"created_at":"20